               <head>Miscellaneous works of Sufi poetry, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Fragments of a miscellaneous collection of poetic works on Sufi subjects. Volume not dated; item a dated separately (26 Rajab 1139/19 March 1727). Scribal shikastah āmīz and rough naskh for Arabic, by multiple hands. Limited annotations in margins. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged (brown leather lacking pasteboards, broken spine), labelled. Folios mostly bound; cropped, tears, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1124E-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="55r">ff. 1r-55r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Fragment of an untitled mas̲navī on Sufism by an unnamed author.
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 55r): completed salkh (28) of Isfandārmāh, 26 Rajab 1139/19 March 1727. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1124E-item2">
                     <locus from="56v" to="144r">ff. 56v-144r</locus>
